<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="272" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1105,2029]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1105,1130]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body pale yellow with wide median brown band extending from apex of crown to apex of forewings (Figs 0 1, 13); pygofer with paired dentiform processes on ventral margin (Fig. 05); subgenital plates with macrosetae at apex (Figs 0 6, 07); style with preapical lobe developed and protruded laterally (Figs 0 8, 09); aedeagus long and slender with one pair of lateroapical processes (
<figureCitation box="[914,1046,1213,1237]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[237,1369,219,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[212,1369,195,1896]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Tozzita bifida sp. nov., male holotype: 0 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 0 2, head, frontal view; 0 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 0 4, forewing; 0 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 0 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 0 7, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 0 8, style, lateral view; 0 9, connective and styles, dorsal view; 10, aedeagus, lateral view; 11, aedeagus, dorsal view; 12, aedeagus, posterodorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221614/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">
Figs 
<number box="[972,1046,1213,1237]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
</figureCitation>
); anal tube with paired bifid basal processes (Fig. 05).
</paragraph>
