<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1105,2029]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,371,1393,1418]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">General color.</emphasis>
Body pale yellow with wide median brown band extending from apex of crown to apex of forewings and orange maculae laterally to this band (
<figureCitation box="[760,832,1429,1453]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[237,1369,219,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[212,1369,195,1896]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Tozzita bifida sp. nov., male holotype: 0 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 0 2, head, frontal view; 0 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 0 4, forewing; 0 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 0 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 0 7, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 0 8, style, lateral view; 0 9, connective and styles, dorsal view; 10, aedeagus, lateral view; 11, aedeagus, dorsal view; 12, aedeagus, posterodorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221614/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[848,923,1429,1453]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15. 13 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1159,1182]" captionTargetBox="[481,1101,193,1125]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[472,1115,193,1138]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. 13 – 14 Tozzita bifida sp. nov., male holotype: 13, dorsal view; 14, lateral view. 15 Tozzita ips Kramer, male, 15, dorsal view. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221615/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">
13, 
<number box="[892,923,1429,1453]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Crown pale yellow, with two orange bands laterad of median brown band, two circular dark brown spots near anterior margin of crown, apex with black spot, extending ventrally to frons and easily visible in frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[846,948,1501,1525]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[237,1369,219,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[212,1369,195,1896]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Tozzita bifida sp. nov., male holotype: 0 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 0 2, head, frontal view; 0 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 0 4, forewing; 0 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 0 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 0 7, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 0 8, style, lateral view; 0 9, connective and styles, dorsal view; 10, aedeagus, lateral view; 11, aedeagus, dorsal view; 12, aedeagus, posterodorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221614/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">
Figs 
<number box="[903,948,1501,1525]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum pale yellow, with orange lateral margins. Mesonotum pale yellow with two black spots on lateral margins at midlength. Frons, ventral portion of thorax, fore- and mid legs, pale yellow; hind legs orange. Forewings semi-hyaline, basal fourth orange, colorless at median half, apical fourth and commisural margin brown (Fig. 04). Hindwings hyaline. Abdomen pale yellow with brown spots (
<figureCitation box="[302,386,1645,1669]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15. 13 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1159,1182]" captionTargetBox="[481,1101,193,1125]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[472,1115,193,1138]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. 13 – 14 Tozzita bifida sp. nov., male holotype: 13, dorsal view; 14, lateral view. 15 Tozzita ips Kramer, male, 15, dorsal view. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221615/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">
Fig. 
<number box="[355,386,1645,1669]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1105,2029]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,1256,2037]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="274" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1681,1706]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">Description.</emphasis>
Head. Crown, in dorsal view, longer than wide, surface finely punctuated (Fig. 01). Clypeus broad with lateral margins converging apically (Fig. 02), without tuberosity (Fig. 03). Thorax. Pronotum with faint transverse striations. Male genitalia. Pygofer, in lateral view, approximately subquadrangular; setae on posteroventral margin and apex; ventral margin median third with paired dentiform processes, slightly sclerotized; apex slightly sclerotized and curved ventrally, not spatulate (Fig. 05). Subgenital plates completely fused except apically; longer than pygofer; basal third with few short setae on lateral margins and preapical portion of dorsal surface; apical third with slender setae on lateral margins; apex rounded with macrosetae; middle third, in ventral view, compressed laterally (Fig. 06); dorsal margin, in lateral view, sinuous, wide at base and with preapical portion narrowed at apical two-thirds (Fig. 07). Styles, in lateral view, moderately long and slender; apical third more robust, elongated and sclerotized, slightly curved ventrally; with few setae on ventral margin; preapical lobe developed laterally and produced posteriorly, apex rounded (Figs 0 8, 09). Connective, in dorsal view, V-shaped; about two-thirds the length of styles; articulated to the basis of the aedeagus (Fig. 09). Aedeagus long and slender; with shaft curved dorsoanteriorly; apical half flattened dorsoventrally; one pair of lateroapical processes, slender, sinuous and acute; preatrium about half length of shaft; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation box="[1024,1160,1364,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[237,1369,219,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[212,1369,195,1896]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Tozzita bifida sp. nov., male holotype: 0 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 0 2, head, frontal view; 0 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 0 4, forewing; 0 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 0 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 0 7, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 0 8, style, lateral view; 0 9, connective and styles, dorsal view; 10, aedeagus, lateral view; 11, aedeagus, dorsal view; 12, aedeagus, posterodorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221614/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="274">
Figs 
<number box="[1085,1160,1364,1388]" pageId="4" pageNumber="274" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Anal tube moderately sclerotized at base; with one pair of basal process, strongly sclerotized, curved dorsally, flattened dorsoventrally and bifid at apical third (Fig. 05). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
